56 qboolean G_ScriptAction_SetModelFromBrushmodel(gentity_t *ent, char *params)
57 {
58  char *pString = params;
59  char *token;
60  char modelname[MAX_QPATH];
61  int i;
62  qboolean solid = qtrue;
63 
64  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
65 
66  if (!token[0])
67  {
68  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_SetModelFromBrushmodel: setmodelfrombrushmodel must have an targetname\n");
69  }
70  Q_strncpyz(modelname, token, MAX_QPATH);
71 
72  ent->r.svFlags &= ~SVF_IGNOREBMODELEXTENTS;
73 
74  while (*token)
75  {
76  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "useoriginforpvs"))
77  {
78  ent->r.svFlags |= SVF_IGNOREBMODELEXTENTS;
79  }
80  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "nonsolid"))
81  {
82  solid = qfalse;
83  }
84 
85  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
86  }
87 
88  if (modelname[0] == '*')
89  {
90  trap_SetBrushModel(ent, modelname);
91 
92  if (!solid)
93  {
94  ent->s.eFlags |= EF_NONSOLID_BMODEL;
95  ent->clipmask = 0;
96  ent->r.contents = 0;
97  trap_LinkEntity(ent);
98  }
99 
100  return qtrue;
101  }
102  else
103  {
104  for (i = 0; i < level.numBrushModels; i++)
105  {
106  if (!Q_stricmp(level.brushModelInfo[i].modelname, modelname))
107  {
108  trap_SetBrushModel(ent, va("*%i", level.brushModelInfo[i].model));
109 
110  if (!solid)
111  {
112  ent->s.eFlags |= EF_NONSOLID_BMODEL;
113  ent->clipmask = 0;
114  ent->r.contents = 0;
115 
116  trap_LinkEntity(ent);
117  }
118 
119  return qtrue;
120  }
121  }
122  }
123 
124  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_SetModelFromBrushmodel: setmodelfrombrushmodel target not found %s\n", modelname);
125 
126  return qtrue;
127 }

135 qboolean G_ScriptAction_SetPosition(gentity_t *ent, char *params)

140 
141  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);

143  {
144  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_SetPosition: setposition must have an targetname\n");

146 
147  if ((pPathCorner = BG_Find_PathCorner(token)))

296 qboolean G_ScriptAction_FollowPath(gentity_t *ent, char *params)
297 {
298  char *pString, *token;
299 
300  if (params && (ent->scriptStatus.scriptFlags & SCFL_GOING_TO_MARKER))
301  {
302  // we can't process a new movement until the last one has finished
303  return qfalse;
304  }
305 
306  if (!params || ent->scriptStatus.scriptStackChangeTime < level.time) // we are waiting for it to reach destination
307  {
308  if (ent->s.pos.trTime + ent->s.pos.trDuration <= level.time) // we made it
309  {
310  ent->scriptStatus.scriptFlags &= ~SCFL_GOING_TO_MARKER;
311 
312  // set the angles at the destination
313  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&ent->s.apos, ent->s.apos.trTime + ent->s.apos.trDuration, ent->s.angles, qtrue, ent->s.effect2Time);
314  VectorCopy(ent->s.angles, ent->s.apos.trBase);
315  VectorCopy(ent->s.angles, ent->r.currentAngles);
316  ent->s.apos.trTime = level.time;
317  ent->s.apos.trDuration = 0;
318  ent->s.apos.trType = TR_STATIONARY;
319  VectorClear(ent->s.apos.trDelta);
320 
321  // stop moving
322  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&ent->s.pos, level.time, ent->s.origin, qfalse, ent->s.effect2Time);
323  VectorCopy(ent->s.origin, ent->s.pos.trBase);
324  VectorCopy(ent->s.origin, ent->r.currentOrigin);
325  ent->s.pos.trTime = level.time;
326  ent->s.pos.trDuration = 0;
327  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_STATIONARY;
328  VectorClear(ent->s.pos.trDelta);
329 
330  script_linkentity(ent);
331 
332  return qtrue;
333  }
334  }
335  else // we have just started this command
336  {
337  splinePath_t *pSpline;
338  float speed;
339  float length = 0;
340  float dist;
341  int backward;
342  int i;
343  qboolean wait = qfalse;
344 
345  pString = params;
346 
347  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
348  if (!token[0])
349  {
350  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowPath: followpath must have a direction\n");
351  }
352 
353  backward = atoi(token);
354 
355  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
356  if (!token[0])
357  {
358  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowPath: followpath must have a targetname\n");
359  }
360 
361  if (!(pSpline = BG_Find_Spline(token)))
362  {
363  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowPath: can't find spline with \"targetname\" = \"%s\"\n", token);
364  }
365 
366  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
367  if (!token[0])
368  {
369  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowPath: followpath must have a speed\n");
370  }
371 
372  speed = (float)(atof(token));
373 
374  while (token[0])
375  {
376  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
377  if (token[0])
378  {
379  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "wait"))
380  {
381  wait = qtrue;
382  }
383 
384  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "length"))
385  {
386  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
387  if (!token[0])
388  {
389  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowPath: length must have a value\n");
390  }
391 
392  length = atoi(token);
393  }
394  }
395  }
396 
397  // calculate the trajectory
398  ent->s.apos.trType = ent->s.pos.trType = TR_LINEAR_PATH;
399  ent->s.apos.trTime = ent->s.pos.trTime = level.time;
400 
401  ent->s.apos.trBase[0] = length;
402 
403  ent->s.effect2Time = backward ? -(pSpline - splinePaths + 1) : pSpline - splinePaths + 1;
404 
405  VectorClear(ent->s.pos.trDelta);
406 
407  dist = 0;
408  for (i = 0; i < MAX_SPLINE_SEGMENTS; i++)
409  {
410  dist += pSpline->segments[i].length;
411  }
412 
413  ent->s.apos.trDuration = ent->s.pos.trDuration = (int)(1000 * (dist / speed));
414 
415  if (!wait)
416  {
417  // round the duration to the next 50ms
418  if (ent->s.pos.trDuration % 50)
419  {
420  float frac = (float)(((ent->s.pos.trDuration / 50) * 50 + 50) - ent->s.pos.trDuration) / (float)(ent->s.pos.trDuration);
421 
422  if (frac < 1)
423  {
424  ent->s.apos.trDuration = ent->s.pos.trDuration = (ent->s.pos.trDuration / 50) * 50 + 50;
425  }
426  }
427 
428  // set the goto flag, so we can keep processing the move until we reach the destination
429  ent->scriptStatus.scriptFlags |= SCFL_GOING_TO_MARKER;
430  return qtrue; // continue to next command
431  }
432  }
433 
434  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&ent->s.pos, level.time, ent->r.currentOrigin, qfalse, ent->s.effect2Time);
435  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&ent->s.apos, level.time, ent->r.currentAngles, qtrue, ent->s.effect2Time);
436  script_linkentity(ent);
437 
438  return qfalse;
439 }

513 qboolean G_ScriptAction_StartAnimation(gentity_t *ent, char *params)
514 {
515  int fps = 0;
516  char *pString = params;
517  char *token;
518  qboolean norandom = qfalse;
519  qboolean nolerp = qfalse;
520  qboolean noloop = qfalse;
521 
522  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
523  if (!token[0])
524  {
525  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_StartAnimation: startanimation must have a start frame\n");
526  }
527 
528  ent->s.legsAnim = atoi(token);
529 
530  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
531  if (!token[0])
532  {
533  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_StartAnimation: startanimation must have a frame count\n");
534  }
535 
536  ent->s.torsoAnim = atoi(token);
537 
538  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
539  if (!token[0])
540  {
541  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_StartAnimation: startanimation must have a fps rate\n");
542  }
543 
544  fps = atoi(token);
545 
546  // this is fps to animate with
547  if (fps > 0)
548  {
549  ent->s.weapon = (int)(1000.f / fps);
550  }
551  else
552  {
553  ent->s.weapon = 50; // default misc gamemodel 1000/20
554  if (g_scriptDebug.integer)
555  {
556  G_Printf("G_ScriptAction_StartAnimation: startanimation fps rate of entity %s %s must have a value > 0 - <fps> is set to 20\n", ent->classname, ent->targetname);
557  }
558  }
559 
560  while (token[0])
561  {
562  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
563  if (token[0])
564  {
565  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "norandom"))
566  {
567  norandom = qtrue;
568  }
569 
570  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "nolerp"))
571  {
572  nolerp = qtrue;
573  }
574 
575  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "noloop"))
576  {
577  noloop = qtrue;
578  }
579  }
580  }
581 
582  if (norandom)
583  {
584  ent->s.frame = 0;
585  }
586  else
587  {
588  ent->s.frame = rand() % ent->s.torsoAnim;
589  }
590 
591  if (noloop)
592  {
593  ent->s.clientNum = 1;
594  }
595  else
596  {
597  ent->s.clientNum = 0;
598  }
599 
600  if (nolerp)
601  {
602  ent->s.animMovetype++;
603  }
604 
605  return qtrue;
606 }

614 qboolean G_ScriptAction_SetSpeed(gentity_t *ent, char *params)
615 {
616  vec3_t speed;
617  char *pString = params;
618  int i;
619  char *token;
620  qboolean gravity = qfalse;
621  qboolean lowgravity = qfalse;
622 
623  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&ent->s.pos, level.time, ent->r.currentOrigin, qtrue, ent->s.effect2Time);
624  VectorCopy(ent->r.currentOrigin, ent->s.pos.trBase);
625 
626  for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
627  {
628  token = COM_Parse(&pString);
629  if (!token[0])
630  {
631  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_SetSpeed: syntax: setspeed <x> <y> <z> [gravity|lowgravity]\n");
632  }
633  speed[i] = atoi(token);
634  }
635 
636  while ((token = COM_Parse(&pString)) && *token)
637  {
638  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "gravity"))
639  {
640  gravity = qtrue;
641  }
642  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "lowgravity"))
643  {
644  lowgravity = qtrue;
645  }
646  }
647 
648  if (gravity)
649  {
650  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_GRAVITY;
651  }
652  else if (lowgravity)
653  {
654  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_GRAVITY_LOW;
655  }
656  else
657  {
658  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_LINEAR;
659  }
660  ent->s.pos.trTime = level.time;
661 
662  VectorCopy(speed, ent->s.pos.trDelta);
663 
664  script_linkentity(ent);
665 
666  return qtrue;
667 }

807  int bufferIndex;
808 
809  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
810  if (!token[0])
811  {
812  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowSpline: globalaccum without a buffer index\n");
813  }
814 
815  bufferIndex = atoi(token);
816  if (bufferIndex < 0 || bufferIndex >= G_MAX_SCRIPT_ACCUM_BUFFERS)
817  {
818  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowSpline: globalaccum buffer is outside range (0 - %i)\n", G_MAX_SCRIPT_ACCUM_BUFFERS - 1);
819  }
820 
821  backward = level.globalAccumBuffer[bufferIndex] != 0 ? qtrue : qfalse;
822  }
823  else
824  {
825  backward = atoi(token);
826  }
827 
828  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
829  if (!token[0])
830  {
831  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowSpline: followspline must have an targetname\n");
832  }
833 
834  if (!(pSpline = BG_Find_Spline(token)))
835  {
836  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowSpline: can't find spline with \"targetname\" = \"%s\"\n", token);
837  }
838 
839  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
840  if (!token[0])
841  {
842  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowSpline: followspline must have a speed\n");
843  }
844 
845  speed = (float)(atof(token)) * g_moverScale.value;
846 
847  while (token[0])
848  {
849  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
850  if (token[0])
851  {
852  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "wait"))
853  {
854  wait = qtrue;
855  }
856 
857  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "length"))
858  {
859  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
860  if (!token[0])
861  {
862  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowSpline: length must have a value\n");
863  }
864 
865  length = atoi(token);
866  }
867 
868  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "roll"))
869  {
870  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
871  if (!token[0])
872  {
873  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowSpline: roll must have a start angle\n");
874  }
875 
876  roll[0] = atoi(token);
877 
878  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
879  if (!token[0])
880  {
881  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_FollowSpline: roll must have an end angle\n");
882  }
883 
884  roll[1] = atoi(token);
885  }
886 
887  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "dampin"))
888  {
889  if (roll[0] >= 0)
890  {
891  roll[0] += 1000;
892  }
893  else
894  {
895  roll[0] -= 1000;
896  }
897  }
898 
899  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "dampout"))
900  {
901  if (roll[0] >= 0)
902  {
903  roll[0] += 10000;
904  }
905  else
906  {
907  roll[0] -= 10000;
908  }
909  }
910  }
911  }
912 
913  // calculate the trajectory
914  ent->s.apos.trType = ent->s.pos.trType = TR_SPLINE;
915  ent->s.apos.trTime = ent->s.pos.trTime = level.time;
916 
917  ent->s.apos.trBase[0] = length;
918  ent->s.apos.trBase[1] = roll[0];
919  ent->s.apos.trBase[2] = roll[1];
920 
921  ent->s.effect2Time = backward ? -(pSpline - splinePaths + 1) : pSpline - splinePaths + 1;
922 
923  VectorClear(ent->s.pos.trDelta);
924  ent->s.apos.trDuration = ent->s.pos.trDuration = (int)(1000 * (pSpline->length / speed));
925 
926  if (!wait)
927  {
928  // round the duration to the next 50ms
929  if (ent->s.pos.trDuration % 50)
930  {
931  float frac = (float)(((ent->s.pos.trDuration / 50) * 50 + 50) - ent->s.pos.trDuration) / (float)(ent->s.pos.trDuration);
932 
933  if (frac < 1)
934  {
935  ent->s.apos.trDuration = ent->s.pos.trDuration = (ent->s.pos.trDuration / 50) * 50 + 50;
936  }
937  }
938 
939  // set the goto flag, so we can keep processing the move until we reach the destination
940  ent->scriptStatus.scriptFlags |= SCFL_GOING_TO_MARKER;
941  return qtrue; // continue to next command
942  }
943 
944  }
945 
946  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&ent->s.pos, level.time, ent->r.currentOrigin, qfalse, ent->s.effect2Time);
947  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&ent->s.apos, level.time, ent->r.currentAngles, qtrue, ent->s.effect2Time);
948  script_linkentity(ent);
949 
950  return qfalse;
951 }

1376 qboolean G_ScriptAction_GotoMarker(gentity_t *ent, char *params)
1377 {
1378  char *pString, *token;
1379  gentity_t *target = NULL;
1380  vec3_t vec;
1381  trType_t trType;
1382  vec3_t diff;
1383  vec3_t angles;
1384 
1385  if (params && (ent->scriptStatus.scriptFlags & SCFL_GOING_TO_MARKER))
1386  {
1387  // we can't process a new movement until the last one has finished
1388  return qfalse;
1389  }
1390 
1391  if (!params || ent->scriptStatus.scriptStackChangeTime < level.time) // we are waiting for it to reach destination
1392  {
1393  if (ent->s.pos.trTime + ent->s.pos.trDuration <= level.time) // we made it
1394  {
1395  ent->scriptStatus.scriptFlags &= ~SCFL_GOING_TO_MARKER;
1396 
1397  // set the angles at the destination
1398  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&ent->s.apos, ent->s.apos.trTime + ent->s.apos.trDuration, ent->s.angles, qtrue, ent->s.effect2Time);
1399  VectorCopy(ent->s.angles, ent->s.apos.trBase);
1400  VectorCopy(ent->s.angles, ent->r.currentAngles);
1401  ent->s.apos.trTime = level.time;
1402  ent->s.apos.trDuration = 0;
1403  ent->s.apos.trType = TR_STATIONARY;
1404  VectorClear(ent->s.apos.trDelta);
1405 
1406  // stop moving
1407  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&ent->s.pos, level.time, ent->s.origin, qfalse, ent->s.effect2Time);
1408  VectorCopy(ent->s.origin, ent->s.pos.trBase);
1409  VectorCopy(ent->s.origin, ent->r.currentOrigin);
1410  ent->s.pos.trTime = level.time;
1411  ent->s.pos.trDuration = 0;
1412  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_STATIONARY;
1413  VectorClear(ent->s.pos.trDelta);
1414 
1415  script_linkentity(ent);
1416 
1417  return qtrue;
1418  }
1419  }
1420  else // we have just started this command
1421  {
1422  pathCorner_t *pPathCorner;
1423  float speed, dist;
1424  int i, duration;
1425  qboolean wait = qfalse, turntotarget = qfalse;
1426 
1427  pString = params;
1428  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
1429  if (!token[0])
1430  {
1431  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_GotoMarker: gotomarker must have an targetname\n");
1432  }
1433 
1434  if ((pPathCorner = BG_Find_PathCorner(token)))
1435  {
1436  VectorSubtract(pPathCorner->origin, ent->r.currentOrigin, vec);
1437  }
1438  else
1439  {
1440  // find the entity with the given "targetname"
1441  // FIXME: optimize ... is this used for players?
1442  target = G_FindByTargetname(NULL, token);
1443 
1444  if (!target)
1445  {
1446  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_GotoMarker: can't find entity with \"targetname\" = \"%s\"\n", token);
1447  }
1448 
1449  VectorSubtract(target->r.currentOrigin, ent->r.currentOrigin, vec);
1450  }
1451 
1452  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
1453  if (!token[0])
1454  {
1455  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_GotoMarker: gotomarker must have a speed\n");
1456  }
1457 
1458  speed = (float)atof(token);
1459  trType = TR_LINEAR_STOP;
1460 
1461  while (token[0])
1462  {
1463  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
1464  if (token[0])
1465  {
1466  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "accel"))
1467  {
1468  trType = TR_ACCELERATE;
1469  }
1470  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "deccel"))
1471  {
1472  trType = TR_DECCELERATE;
1473  }
1474  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "wait"))
1475  {
1476  wait = qtrue;
1477  }
1478  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "turntotarget"))
1479  {
1480  turntotarget = qtrue;
1481  }
1482  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "relative"))
1483  {
1484  gentity_t *target2;
1485  pathCorner_t *pPathCorner2;
1486  vec3_t vec2 = { 0 };
1487 
1488  token = COM_ParseExt(&pString, qfalse);
1489 
1490  if ((pPathCorner2 = BG_Find_PathCorner(token)))
1491  {
1492  VectorCopy(pPathCorner2->origin, vec2);
1493  }
1494  else if ((target2 = G_FindByTargetname(NULL, token))) // FIXME: optimize ... is this used for players?
1495  {
1496  VectorCopy(target2->r.currentOrigin, vec2);
1497  }
1498  else
1499  {
1500  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_GotoMarker: Target for relative gotomarker not found: %s\n", token);
1501  }
1502 
1503  VectorAdd(vec, ent->r.currentOrigin, vec);
1504  VectorSubtract(vec, vec2, vec);
1505  }
1506  }
1507  }
1508 
1509  // start the movement
1510  if (ent->s.eType == ET_MOVER)
1511  {
1512  VectorCopy(vec, ent->movedir);
1513  VectorCopy(ent->r.currentOrigin, ent->pos1);
1514  VectorAdd(ent->r.currentOrigin, vec, ent->pos2);
1515  ent->speed = speed * g_moverScale.value;
1516  dist = VectorDistance(ent->pos1, ent->pos2);
1517  // setup the movement with the new parameters
1518  InitMover(ent);
1519 
1520  if (ent->s.eType == ET_MOVER && (ent->spawnflags & 8))
1521  {

1530  ent->s.pos.trType = trType;
1531  }

1566  }

4942 qboolean G_ScriptAction_Delete(gentity_t *ent, char *params)
4943 {
4944  gentity_t *found = NULL;
4945  char *token;
4946  char *p = params;
4947  char key[MAX_TOKEN_CHARS], value[MAX_TOKEN_CHARS];
4948  int i;
4949  int pass[MAX_GENTITIES]; // number of matching criteria for each entity
4950  int count = 0; // number of key/value pairs in params
4951  int deleted = 0; // number of deleted entities
4952  qboolean terminate = qfalse;
4953  int valueInt;
4954  float valueFloat;
4955  vec3_t valueVector;
4956 
4957  // params can contain more than 1 key/value pair,
4958  // We must check if the entity equals all of these pairs
4959  // before we delete it..
4960  for (i = MAX_CLIENTS; i < MAX_GENTITIES; ++i)
4961  {
4962  pass[i] = 0;
4963  }
4964 
4965  while (!terminate)
4966  {
4967  // strip key/value from the params..
4968  token = COM_ParseExt(&p, qfalse);
4969 
4970  // are there tokes in the params?..
4971  if (!token[0])
4972  {
4973  break;
4974  }
4975 
4976  strcpy(key, token);
4977 
4978  token = COM_ParseExt(&p, qfalse);
4979  if (!token[0])
4980  {
4981  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_Delete(): key \"%s\" has no value", key);
4982  }
4983 
4984  strcpy(value, token);
4985 
4986  // does the field exist?..
4987  for (i = 0; fields[i].name; ++i)
4988  if (!Q_stricmp(fields[i].name, key))
4989  {
4990  break;
4991  }
4992  if (!fields[i].name)
4993  {
4994  G_Error("G_ScriptAction_Delete(): non-existing key \"%s\"", key);
4995  }
4996 
4997  // we have a key/value pair to search for..
4998  count++;
4999 
5000  // start searching from the first entity..
5001  found = NULL;
5002 
5003  // check key's datatype..
5004  switch (fields[i].type)
5005  {
5006  case F_INT:
5007  valueInt = atoi(value);
5008  // find all entities with the given key/value..
5009  while ((found = G_FindInt(found, fields[i].ofs, valueInt)) != NULL)
5010  {
5011  pass[found->s.number]++;
5012  }
5013  break;
5014 
5015  case F_FLOAT:
5016  valueFloat = (float)atof(value);
5017  while ((found = G_FindFloat(found, fields[i].ofs, valueFloat)) != NULL)
5018  {
5019  pass[found->s.number]++;
5020  }
5021  break;
5022 
5023  case F_LSTRING:
5024  case F_GSTRING:
5025  while ((found = G_Find(found, fields[i].ofs, value)) != NULL)
5026  {
5027  pass[found->s.number]++;
5028  }
5029  break;
5030 
5031  case F_VECTOR:
5032  sscanf(value, "%f %f %f", &valueVector[0], &valueVector[1], &valueVector[2]);
5033  while ((found = G_FindVector(found, fields[i].ofs, valueVector)) != NULL)
5034  {
5035  pass[found->s.number]++;
5036  }
5037  break;
5038 
5039  case F_ANGLEHACK:
5040  valueVector[0] = 0;
5041  valueVector[1] = (float)atof(value);
5042  valueVector[2] = 0;
5043  while ((found = G_FindVector(found, fields[i].ofs, valueVector)) != NULL)
5044  {
5045  pass[found->s.number]++;
5046  }
5047  break;
5048 
5049  case F_ENTITY:
5050  case F_ITEM:
5051  case F_CLIENT:
5052  case F_IGNORE:
5053  default:
5054  // It's certain the test will fail now, so just abort..
5055  G_Printf("WARNING G_ScriptAction_Delete(): invalid key \"%s\"", key);
5056  terminate = qtrue;
5057  break;
5058  }
5059  }
5060 
5061  // did we find any key/value pairs in the params at all?..
5062  if (count == 0)
5063  {
5064  return qfalse;
5065  }
5066 
5067  // now delete the entities that passed all tests..
5068  for (i = MAX_GENTITIES - 1; i >= MAX_CLIENTS; i--)
5069  if (pass[i] == count)
5070  {
5071  deleted++;
5072  G_Printf("G_ScriptAction_Delete(): \"%s\" entity %i removed (%s)\n", g_entities[i].classname, i, params);
5073  G_FreeEntity(&g_entities[i]);
5074  }
5075 
5076  // did we actually delete any entity?..
5077  if (deleted > 0)
5078  {
5079  return qtrue;
5080  }
5081  else
5082  {
5083  G_Printf("G_ScriptAction_Delete(): no entities found (%s)\n", params);
5084  }
5085  return qfalse;
5086 }
